<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,434,459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Description.</emphasis>
Body translucent whitish overall. Vertex with two round opaque white patches between coronal suture and eyes. Pronotum with two symmetrical L-shaped opaque white patches. Scutellum opaque whitish medially; triangles pale yellow, terminal part of scutellum yellow. Forewing with basal half mostly opaque ivory, with large transverse reddish-brown medial band, apical cells transparent and infumated lightly; 1st apical cell smallest, 2nd apical cell largest (
<figureCitation box="[516,648,578,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 20–22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
Abdominal apodemes nearly extending to apex of 7th segment. Pygofer side with several rigid setae at hind margin, and with large triangular lobe at ventro-caudal angle (
<figureCitation box="[851,983,650,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with triangular lateral protrusion subapically, with 2 small rigid setae and 1 peg-like seta apically (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1169,686,711]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
). Paramere with lateral margin broadly rounded distad of connective, medial margin with several irregularly arranged sensory pits, apex curved slightly and abruptly tapered (
<figureCitation box="[570,654,758,783]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft bending gently and inflated near midlength in lateral view, with two pairs of processes; apical ventral processes long, slender and asymmetrical, one serrate apically and extended laterad, other curved to shaft; dorsal processes near midlength short and thin (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1260,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 29–31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
