<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1010,1035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Notes.</emphasis>
The reddish-brown pattern and genital characteristics of the new species are unique in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,288,1046,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Guheswaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Guheswaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
excepting that the crown with two large white patches and shape of connective are similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thapa." authorityName="Thapa." class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Guheswaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linguplata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">G. linguplata</emphasis>
Thapa.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
